  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and chop <strong>half </strong>your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges, then finely slice the <strong>remaining brown onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-7-1699434889303-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-7-1699434889303-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-7-1699434889303-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-7-1699434889303-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-7-1699434889303-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to one side of the baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>ground turmeric</strong>, <strong>black mustard seeds </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>curry powder </strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>Bombay potatoes</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-8-1699434901703-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-8-1699434901703-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-8-1699434901703-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-8-1699434901703-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-8-1699434901703-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>paneer</strong> into<strong> </strong>4<strong> </strong>strips per person</p><p>Wash, then rip the leaves off your <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-7-1699434908757-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-7-1699434908757-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-7-1699434908757-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-7-1699434908757-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-7-1699434908757-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garam masala </strong>(save the rest for later!) to a plate with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>paneer strips</strong> to the plate and turn them several times until fully coated</p><p>After the Bombay potatoes have had an initial 15 min, add the <strong>coated paneer</strong> to the other side of the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-7-1699434928235-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-7-1699434928235-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-7-1699434928235-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-7-1699434928235-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-7-1699434928235-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 12-15 min, or until the potatoes are crispy and golden and the paneer is charred – this is your <strong>curried paneer & Bombay potato tray bake</strong></p><p>Line a separate baking tray with a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>and add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> to the middle of the foil with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil to form a sealed parcel and put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until the greens are tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-7-1699434933313-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-7-1699434933313-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-7-1699434933313-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-7-1699434933313-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-7-1699434933313-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the onion has started to soften</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-7-1699434942616-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-7-1699434942616-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-7-1699434942616-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-7-1699434942616-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-7-1699434942616-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>and <strong>garam masala</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Once thickened, remove the pan from the heat and stir through <strong>half</strong> your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> – this is your <strong>masala sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-7-1699434949349-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-7-1699434949349-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-7-1699434949349-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-7-1699434949349-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-7-1699434949349-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>curried paneer</strong> on a plate with the <strong>Bombay potatoes </strong>and <strong>spring greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon the <strong>masala sauce</strong> over the paneer and drizzle over the <strong>remaining natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
